## Proposal 
### Problem
The popup moves to the side if the page is resized

### Root Cause
We dont have the logic setup to reposition the popover when the window resizes in Wallet Page>

### Changes
setup a listner to window change usinf Dimensions Api and reset position on window change.

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
        const popoverPositionListener = Dimensions.addEventListener('change', () => {
            if (!shouldListenForResize) {
                return;
            }
            if (shouldShowAddPaymentMenu || shouldShowDefaultDeleteMenu) {
                setMenuPosition();
            }
        });
        return () => {
            if (!popoverPositionListener) {
                return;
            }
            popoverPositionListener.remove();
        }
    }, [shouldShowAddPaymentMenu, shouldShowDefaultDeleteMenu, setMenuPosition, shouldListenForResize]);
```
we also need to have the ListFooterComponent outside the FlashList in `PaymentMethodList` due to internal implementation of FlashList somehow when window is resized the `target.getBoundingClientRect()` it returns 0 for every value and delay before setting the new position for `AddPaymentMethodMenu` otherwise when quickly resizing the dimensions when `AddPaymentMethodMenu` is open may gets wrong position of anchor element

@Victor-Nyagudi I disagree with you, this is a totally different issue. By the way, the title of this issue brings misunderstanding that it seems it is related with the delete modal on Wallet but the case is as commented in my [proposal](https://github.com/Expensify/App/issues/31706#issuecomment-1823347399) it is a regression caused when migrating `PopoverReportActionContextMenu` from class component to functional component and the bug is breaking the popover mechanism to reposition itself on dimension change and now every context menu we have is broken (in terms of repositioning) and this bug should be fixed ASAP.
Look as this video 👍 

https://github.com/Expensify/App/assets/38649957/c1533975-6141-4b82-9691-c75a158660f6

I dont think holding for linked issue makes sense, as linked pr change to delete confirmation to a modal instead of popover the repositioning issue is gone here but the other popovers `Add Bank Account` and "delete or Make Default payment method" will have the repositioning issue and its not going to be solved with linked PR and the solution for this issue should aim to solve that without touching the popovers itself

> it is a regression caused when migrating PopoverReportActionContextMenu from class component to functional component and the bug is breaking the popover mechanism to reposition itself on dimension change.

@FitseTLT unless i am missing something here, this particular issue aims to solve the issue for wallet screen popover not the context menu for chat it should be treated as a seperate issue (if it is a issue as far as i guess this is expected for context menu and this does not create any ui inconsistency) you can raise this on slack channel if you are sure this is a issue needs to fixed and there's no GH handling that already
